Twice premium toothpaste is a result of an 18-month research project by brothers Julian and Cody Levine who joined with singer music icon Lenny Kravitz to develop toothpaste that not only tastes great but also helps people smile with confidence. Twice does even more than that! It helps prevent cavities, strengthen tooth enamel, ensure minty-fresh breath, and even fights free radicals. 

A typical combo pack from Twice includes their Early Bird toothpaste which is designed specifically to use in the morning, and Twilight, a toothpaste formula created for evening use. While Early Bird is infused with wintergreen and peppermint, Twilight has a touch of lavender, vanilla, and peppermint. 

Twice is a vegan toothpaste that’s gluten-free, non-toxic, and made using non-GMO ingredients. It is also a cruelty-free toothpaste – neither we they nor our their suppliers test on animals. In fact, we they are a Leaping Bunny certified brand. 

We They also are committed to donating 10% of our profits to the GLO Good Foundation which is an organization that brings healthy smiles to people who cannot afford dental care.

Anyways, perused some of the accessible articles on various tools and their applications along with some of the literature about 'Make' and I thoroughly connected with the overall trajectory of this thing. I found that, in a very short while, even at the ripe old age of 50, 'Make' opened my eyes to a brand new world of possibilities. I look forward to the journey, and not just for myself, but more so perhaps for those younger generations who gather here, those for whom I stand in such awe of; what new worlds you might unveil...If anything, I come here as, yet, another bright and shining instance among so many; proof that the domain of 'wide eyed' wonder, of deep curiosity and enchantment, that sphere so often reserved, exclusive to our youth, does not contract with age, but rather, swells exponentially into, this thing, far more profound and eternal....My hat's off to all of you who make such travel possible.

column6: Scrappy Circuits breaks down the many barriers to teaching and learning invention literacy like pre-requisite skills, cost, and access. It is a modular system of bricks built by the learner and sourced from commonly found objects. Binder clips act as terminals for electricity to travel through each brick and can be connected using alligator clips or homemade Scrappy Clips. The first five Scrappy Circuits bricks, known as the Core Bricks, can be constructed for around a dollar out of some office supplies, an LED tea-light, and an imagination. Larger groups can build these for around twenty dollars and each learner will be able to keep their bricks and continue to explore and invent. The learning doesn't stop there! The Scrappy Circuits journey can continue with many more bricks and projects all made out of common and inexpensive items.
